-Edit inventory under compute as

IP_of_new_node ansible_user=node4 network_interface=br-ex api_interface=br-ex tunnel_interface=br-ex enable_iscsid=no neutron_external_interface="eno1,eno2" neutron_bridge_name="br-ex,br-usrp"

- To test use:
ansible-inventory -i ~/all-in-one --graph
ansible -i ~/all-in-one all -m ping


- In the new node make it no_password
- In the new node install the following:

*  curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com -o get-docker.sh
   sudo sh get-docker.sh
   sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
   newgrp docker
   -- check with docker ps

*  sudo apt install -y python3-docker
*  sudo apt install -y openvswitch-switch
- In the new node configure the netplan



- kolla-ansible  bootstrap-servers -i all-in-one --limit IP_of_new_node
- kolla-ansible  prechecks -i all-in-one --limit IP_of_new_node
- kolla-ansible  pull -i all-in-one --limit IP_of_new_node
- kolla-ansible  deploy -i all-in-one --limit IP_of_new_node --skip-tags openvswitch
